{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775892318524,"sessionID":"ses_28491f670ffeCmvLep0rhd4mmZ","part":{"id":"prt_d7b6e3eb1001jvcPnzozPoUE26","messageID":"msg_d7b6e3351001yYfBcE1BvkkOcw","sessionID":"ses_28491f670ffeCmvLep0rhd4mmZ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_6112d5018516409eb902304e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-041/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-041/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-041: E2E йӣҶжҲҗжөӢиҜ•\n2: \n3: ## 1. Purpose\n4: \n5: дёә AgentCube йЎ№зӣ®жһ„е»әе…Ёйқўзҡ„з«ҜеҲ°з«ҜпјҲE2EпјүйӣҶжҲҗжөӢиҜ•жЎҶжһ¶пјҢйӘҢиҜҒж•ҙдёӘзі»з»ҹд»Һ Kubernetes CRD еҲӣе»әеҲ°д»Јз Ғжү§иЎҢгҖҒAgent и°ғз”Ёзҡ„е®Ңж•ҙй“ҫи·ҜгҖӮ\n6: \n7: жң¬жҸҗжЎҲй’ҲеҜ№ AR-041 йңҖжұӮпјҢеҹәдәҺзҺ°жңүзҡ„ `test/e2e/` жөӢиҜ•еҹәзЎҖи®ҫж–ҪпјҢжү©еұ•д»ҘдёӢж ёеҝғжөӢиҜ•еңәжҷҜпјҡ\n8: \n9: 1. **AgentRuntime з”ҹе‘Ҫе‘Ёжңҹз®ЎзҗҶ** - йӘҢиҜҒ AgentRuntime CRD зҡ„еҲӣе»әгҖҒжӣҙж–°гҖҒеҲ йҷӨеҸҠзҠ¶жҖҒеҗҢжӯҘ\n10: 2. **CodeInterpreter жү§иЎҢжөҒзЁӢ** - йӘҢиҜҒд»Јз Ғи§ЈйҮҠеҷЁзҡ„е®Ңж•ҙжү§иЎҢй“ҫи·ҜпјҲжҸҗдәӨ вҶ’ и°ғеәҰ вҶ’ жү§иЎҢ вҶ’ з»“жһңиҝ”еӣһпјү\n11: 3. **Warm Pool жңәеҲ¶йӘҢиҜҒ** - йӘҢиҜҒ CodeInterpreter жҡ–жұ зҡ„йў„еҲӣе»әгҖҒеӨҚз”Ёе’Ңеӣһж”¶\n12: 4. **Router и·Ҝз”ұе’ҢдјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ** - йӘҢиҜҒиҜ·жұӮи·Ҝз”ұгҖҒдјҡиҜқз»‘е®ҡгҖҒJWT и®ӨиҜҒе’Ң Token з®ЎзҗҶ\n13: 5. **еӨҡз»„д»¶йӣҶжҲҗдәӨдә’** - йӘҢиҜҒ Workload ManagerгҖҒRouterгҖҒSandboxгҖҒPicoD д№Ӣй—ҙзҡ„еҚҸдҪң\n14: \n15: жң¬ E2E жөӢиҜ•жЎҶжһ¶дҪҝз”Ёз”ҹжҲҗзҡ„ `client-go` еә“дёҺ Kubernetes API дәӨдә’пјҢзЎ®дҝқжөӢиҜ•дёҺз”ҹдә§зҺҜеўғиЎҢдёәдёҖиҮҙгҖӮ\n16: \n17: ## 2. Scope\n18: \n19: **Module:** `test/e2e`  \n20: **Language:** Go  \n21: **Size:** L\n22: \n23: ### 2.1 In Scope\n24: \n25: | жөӢиҜ•зұ»еҲ« | жөӢиҜ•ж–Үд»¶ | дјҳе…Ҳзә§ | жөӢиҜ•зұ»еһӢ | дҫқиө– |\n26: |----------|----------|--------|----------|------|\n27: | **AgentRuntime E2E** | | | | |\n28: | AgentRuntime еҲӣе»әе’ҢжҡҙйңІ | `agentruntime_test.go` | P0 | E2E | client-go |\n29: | AgentRuntime зҠ¶жҖҒеҗҢжӯҘ | `agentruntime_status_test.go` | P0 | E2E | client-go, informer |\n30: | AgentRuntime жӣҙж–°е’ҢеҲ йҷӨ | `agentruntime_lifecycle_test.go` | P1 | E2E | client-go |\n31: | AgentRuntime ж Үзӯҫи·Ҝз”ұ | `agentruntime_routing_test.go` | P1 | E2E | Router API |\n32: | **CodeInterpreter E2E** | | | | |\n33: | CodeInterpreter еҲӣе»ә | `codeinterpreter_test.go` | P0 | E2E | client-go |\n34: | д»Јз Ғжү§иЎҢе®Ңж•ҙжөҒзЁӢ | `codeinterpreter_execution_test.go` | P0 | E2E | Router API, PicoD |\n35: | CodeInterpreter зҠ¶жҖҒжңә | `codeinterpreter_status_test.go` | P1 | E2E | client-go |\n36: | Warm Pool жңәеҲ¶ | `codeinterpreter_warmpool_test.go` | P1 | E2E | client-go, Workload Manager API |\n37: | иө„жәҗйҷҗеҲ¶жү§иЎҢ | `codeinterpreter_limits_test.go` | P1 | E2E | PicoD API |\n38: | **Router E2E** | | | | |\n39: | Router еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘ | `router_health_test.go` | P0 | E2E | Router API |\n40: | Invoke жҺҘеҸЈжөӢиҜ• | `router_invoke_test.go` | P0 | E2E | Router API |\n41: | дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶ | `router_session_test.go` | P1 | E2E | Router API, Redis |\n42: | JWT и®ӨиҜҒе’Ң Token з®ЎзҗҶ | `router_auth_test.go` | P1 | E2E | Router API |\n43: | **йӣҶжҲҗеңәжҷҜ** | | | | |\n44: | еӨҡз§ҹжҲ·йҡ”зҰ» | `multi_tenant_test.go` | P2 | E2E | Namespace, RBAC |\n45: | ж•…йҡңжҒўеӨҚ | `failure_recovery_test.go` | P2 | E2E | Chaos Engineering |\n46: | е№¶еҸ‘е’ҢеҺӢеҠӣ | `concurrency_test.go` | P2 | иҙҹиҪҪжөӢиҜ• | Locust/vegeta |\n47: \n48: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n49: \n50: - еҚ•е…ғжөӢиҜ•пјҲз”ұ `pkg/*/` дёӢзҡ„еҚ•е…ғжөӢиҜ•иҰҶзӣ–пјү\n51: - йӣҶжҲҗжөӢиҜ•пјҲз”ұ `test/integration/` иҰҶзӣ–з»„д»¶й—ҙйӣҶжҲҗпјү\n52: - жҖ§иғҪеҹәеҮҶжөӢиҜ•пјҲз”ұеҚ•зӢ¬зҡ„жҖ§иғҪжөӢиҜ•и®ЎеҲ’иҰҶзӣ–пјү\n53: - е®үе…Ёжё—йҖҸжөӢиҜ•пјҲз”ұе®үе…Ёе®Ўи®Ўи®ЎеҲ’иҰҶзӣ–пјү\n54: - PicoD еҶ…йғЁе®һзҺ°з»ҶиҠӮжөӢиҜ•пјҲз”ұ `pkg/picod/` еҚ•е…ғжөӢиҜ•иҰҶзӣ–пјү\n55: \n56: ## 3. Current State Analysis\n57: \n58: ### 3.1 зҺ°жңү E2E жөӢиҜ•еҹәзЎҖи®ҫж–Ҫ\n59: \n60: еҪ“еүҚ `test/e2e/` зӣ®еҪ•еҢ…еҗ«пјҡ\n61: \n62: 1. **Go E2E жөӢиҜ•** (`e2e_test.go`):\n63:    - `TestHealthCheck`: Workload Manager еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘ\n64:    - `TestRouterHealth`: Router еҒҘеә·жЈҖжҹҘ\n65:    - `TestInvokeEchoAgent`: и°ғз”Ё Echo Agent\n66:    - `TestCodeInterpreter`: д»Јз Ғи§ЈйҮҠеҷЁжү§иЎҢ\n67: \n68: 2. **Python E2E жөӢиҜ•** (`test_codeinterpreter.py`):\n69:    - дҪҝз”Ё Python SDK иҝӣиЎҢд»Јз Ғжү§иЎҢжөӢиҜ•\n70: \n71: 3. **жөӢиҜ•и„ҡжң¬** (`run_e2e.sh`):\n72:    - Kind йӣҶзҫӨеҲӣе»әе’Ңз®ЎзҗҶ\n73:    - agent-sandbox CRD е®үиЈ…\n74:    - жң¬ең° Docker й•ңеғҸжһ„е»әе’ҢеҠ иҪҪ\n75:    - Helm е®үиЈ… AgentCube\n76:    - E2E fixtures еә”з”Ё\n77:    - з«ҜеҸЈиҪ¬еҸ‘е’Ң Token з”ҹжҲҗ\n78:    - еӨұиҙҘж—¶ж—Ҙеҝ—ж”¶йӣҶ\n79: \n80: 4. **Fixtures**:\n81:    - `echo_agent.yaml`: Echo Agent е®ҡд№ү\n82:    - `e2e_code_interpreter.yaml`: CodeInterpreter иө„жәҗ\n83:    - `e2e_code_interpreter_warmpool.yaml`: еёҰжҡ–жұ зҡ„ CodeInterpreter\n84: \n85: ### 3.2 Gaps Identified\n86: \n87: 1. **Kubernetes API зӣҙжҺҘжөӢиҜ•зјәеӨұ** - еҪ“еүҚжөӢиҜ•д»…йҖҡиҝҮ HTTP API йӘҢиҜҒпјҢжңӘдҪҝз”Ё client-go зӣҙжҺҘж“ҚдҪң CRD\n88: 2. **зҠ¶жҖҒжңәйӘҢиҜҒдёҚе®Ңж•ҙ** - жңӘйӘҢиҜҒ CRD зҠ¶жҖҒиҪ¬жҚўпјҲPending вҶ’ Running вҶ’ Succeeded/Failedпјү\n89: 3. **Warm Pool жңӘжөӢиҜ•** - жҡ–жұ жңәеҲ¶зҡ„йў„еҲӣе»әгҖҒеӨҚз”Ёе’Ңеӣһж”¶йҖ»иҫ‘жңӘиҰҶзӣ–\n90: 4. **дјҡиҜқз®ЎзҗҶжөӢиҜ•зјәеӨұ** - Router дјҡиҜқз»‘е®ҡгҖҒиҝҮжңҹжё…зҗҶжңӘжөӢиҜ•\n91: 5. **JWT и®ӨиҜҒжөҒзЁӢжңӘиҰҶзӣ–** - Token з”ҹжҲҗгҖҒеҲ·ж–°гҖҒж’Өй”ҖжңӘжөӢиҜ•\n92: 6. **ж•…йҡңеңәжҷҜзјәеӨұ** - ж—  Pod еӨұиҙҘгҖҒзҪ‘з»ңеҲҶеҢәгҖҒиө„жәҗдёҚи¶ізӯүеңәжҷҜжөӢиҜ•\n93: 7. **еӨҡз§ҹжҲ·еңәжҷҜжңӘйӘҢиҜҒ** - Namespace йҡ”зҰ»гҖҒRBAC жқғйҷҗжңӘжөӢиҜ•\n94: \n95: ### 3.3 Client-Go еҹәзЎҖи®ҫж–Ҫ\n96: \n97: ж №жҚ® `deployment/client-go.md`пјҢе·Із”ҹжҲҗе®Ңж•ҙзҡ„ Kubernetes client-go еә“пјҡ\n98: \n99: ```go\n100: // Clientset дҪҝз”ЁзӨәдҫӢ\n101: config, _ := rest.InClusterConfig()\n102: clientset, _ := clientset.NewForConfig(config)\n103: \n104: // иҺ·еҸ– AgentRuntime\n105: runtimeV1alpha1 := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1()\n106: agentRuntimes := runtimeV1alpha1.AgentRuntimes(namespace)\n107: ar, _ := agentRuntimes.Get(ctx, name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n108: \n109: // еҲӣе»ә CodeInterpreter\n110: ci := &runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter{...}\n111: result, _ := runtimeV1alpha1.CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create(ctx, ci, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n112: \n113: // Watch иө„жәҗеҸҳеҢ–\n114: watcher, _ := agentRuntimes.Watch(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n115: for event := range watcher.ResultChan() {\n116:     // еӨ„зҗҶдәӢд»¶\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ### 3.4 Informer жңәеҲ¶\n121: \n122: ```go\n123: // SharedInformerFactory дҪҝз”Ё\n124: factory := externalversions.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 30*time.Second)\n125: informer := factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()\n126: \n127: // ж·»еҠ дәӢд»¶еӨ„зҗҶеҷЁ\n128: informer.Informer().AddEventHandler(cache.ResourceEventHandlerFuncs{\n129:     AddFunc:    func(obj interface{}) { /* ... */ },\n130:     UpdateFunc: func(oldObj, newObj interface{}) { /* ... */ },\n131:     DeleteFunc: func(obj interface{}) { /* ... */ },\n132: })\n133: \n134: // еҗҜеҠЁ Informer\n135: factory.Start(stopCh)\n136: factory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ## 4. Proposed Changes\n140: \n141: ### 4.1 жөӢиҜ•жЎҶжһ¶з»“жһ„\n142: \n143: ```\n144: test/e2e/\n145: в”ңв”Җв”Җ framework/\n146: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ client.go              # Client-go е°ҒиЈ…е’ҢжөӢиҜ•иҫ…еҠ©\n147: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ cluster.go             # Kind йӣҶзҫӨз®ЎзҗҶ\n148: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ fixtures.go            # Test fixtures еҲӣе»әе’Ңз®ЎзҗҶ\n149: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ wait.go                # зӯүеҫ…жқЎд»¶ж»Ўи¶ізҡ„е·Ҙе…·\n150: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ cleanup.go             # иө„жәҗжё…зҗҶ\n151: в”ңв”Җв”Җ agents/\n152: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime_test.go\n153: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime_status_test.go\n154: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ agentruntime_lifecycle_test.go\n155: в”ңв”Җв”Җ code_interpreter/\n156: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_test.go\n157: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_execution_test.go\n158: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_status_test.go\n159: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_warmpool_test.go\n160: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_limits_test.go\n161: в”ңв”Җв”Җ router/\n162: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ router_health_test.go\n163: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ router_invoke_test.go\n164: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ router_session_test.go\n165: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ router_auth_test.go\n166: в”ңв”Җв”Җ integration/\n167: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ multi_tenant_test.go\n168: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ failure_recovery_test.go\n169: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ concurrency_test.go\n170: в”ңв”Җв”Җ fixtures/\n171: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ echo_agent.yaml\n172: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ agentruntime.yaml\n173: в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter.yaml\n174: в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ codeinterpreter_warmpool.yaml\n175: в”ңв”Җв”Җ e2e_test.go                # зҺ°жңүжөӢиҜ•\n176: в”ңв”Җв”Җ run_e2e.sh                 # зҺ°жңүи„ҡжң¬\n177: в””в”Җв”Җ README.md                  # жӣҙж–°ж–ҮжЎЈ\n178: ```\n179: \n180: ### 4.2 ж ёеҝғжөӢиҜ•жЎҶжһ¶ (`framework/`)\n181: \n182: #### 4.2.1 Client-go е°ҒиЈ… (`framework/client.go`)\n183: \n184: ```go\n185: // E2EClient provides a high-level interface for E2E testing\n186: type E2EClient struct {\n187:     kubeClient     kubernetes.Interface\n188:     runtimeClient  clientset.Interface\n189:     restConfig     *rest.Config\n190:     namespace      string\n191:     httpClient     *http.Client\n192:     routerURL      string\n193:     workloadMgrURL string\n194:     apiToken       string\n195: }\n196: \n197: // NewE2EClient creates a new E2E client\n198: func NewE2EClient(namespace string) (*E2EClient, error)\n199: \n200: // KubeClient returns the Kubernetes clientset\n201: func (c *E2EClient) KubeClient() kubernetes.Interface\n202: \n203: // RuntimeClient returns the AgentCube runtime clientset\n204: func (c *E2EClient) RuntimeClient() clientset.Interface\n205: \n206: // CreateAgentRuntime creates an AgentRuntime resource\n207: func (c *E2EClient) CreateAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n208: \n209: // WaitForAgentRuntimeReady waits for AgentRuntime to be ready\n210: func (c *E2EClient) WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx context.Context, name string, timeout time.Duration) error\n211: \n212: // CreateCodeInterpreter creates a CodeInterpreter resource\n213: func (c *E2EClient) CreateCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, ci *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter) error\n214: \n215: // WaitForCodeInterpreterPhase waits for CodeInterpreter to reach a phase\n216: func (c *E2EClient) WaitForCodeInterpreterPhase(ctx context.Context, name string, phase runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterPhase, timeout time.Duration) error\n217: ```\n218: \n219: #### 4.2.2 зӯүеҫ…е·Ҙе…· (`framework/wait.go`)\n220: \n221: ```go\n222: // WaitForCondition waits for a condition to be true\n223: func WaitForCondition(ctx context.Context, name string, timeout time.Duration, condition func() (bool, error)) error\n224: \n225: // WaitForAgentRuntimeReady waits for AgentRuntime status.ready = true\n226: func WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx context.Context, client clientset.Interface, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) error\n227: \n228: // WaitForCodeInterpreterRunning waits for CodeInterpreter phase = Running\n229: func WaitForCodeInterpreterRunning(ctx context.Context, client clientset.Interface, namespace, name string, timeout time.Duration) error\n230: \n231: // WaitForRouterHealth waits for Router health endpoint to return OK\n232: func WaitForRouterHealth(ctx context.Context, routerURL string, timeout time.Duration) error\n233: ```\n234: \n235: #### 4.2.3 Fixtures з®ЎзҗҶ (`framework/fixtures.go`)\n236: \n237: ```go\n238: // AgentRuntimeFixtures provides helper methods to create AgentRuntime resources\n239: type AgentRuntimeFixtures struct{}\n240: \n241: func (f *AgentRuntimeFixtures) NewEchoAgent(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n242: func (f *AgentRuntimeFixtures) NewAgentWithBackendURL(name, namespace, backendURL string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n243: func (f *AgentRuntimeFixtures) NewAgentWithLabels(name, namespace string, labels map[string]string) *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime\n244: \n245: // CodeInterpreterFixtures provides helper methods to create CodeInterpreter resources\n246: type CodeInterpreterFixtures struct{}\n247: \n248: func (f *CodeInterpreterFixtures) NewBasic(name, namespace string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n249: func (f *CodeInterpreterFixtures) NewWithWarmPool(name, namespace string, minIdle, maxIdle int) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n250: func (f *CodeInterpreterFixtures) NewWithResourceLimits(name, namespace string, cpu, memory string) *runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreter\n251: ```\n252: \n253: ### 4.3 AgentRuntime E2E жөӢиҜ•\n254: \n255: #### 4.3.1 еҲӣе»әе’ҢжҡҙйңІжөӢиҜ• (`agents/agentruntime_test.go`)\n256: \n257: ```go\n258: // TestAgentRuntimeCreation tests basic AgentRuntime creation\n259: func TestAgentRuntimeCreation(t *testing.T) {\n260:     client := setupE2EClient(t)\n261:     fixture := &AgentRuntimeFixtures{}\n262:     \n263:     ar := fixture.NewEchoAgent(\"test-echo-agent\", client.Namespace())\n264:     \n265:     // Create\n266:     ctx := context.Background()\n267:     created, err := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n268:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n269:     require.NoError(t, err)\n270:     require.NotNil(t, created)\n271:     \n272:     // Wait for ready\n273:     err = client.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, created.Name, 2*time.Minute)\n274:     require.NoError(t, err)\n275:     \n276:     // Verify status\n277:     status, err := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n278:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Get(ctx, created.Name, metav1.GetOptions{})\n279:     require.NoError(t, err)\n280:     assert.True(t, status.Status.Ready)\n281:     assert.NotNil(t, status.Status.BackendURL)\n282: }\n283: \n284: // TestAgentRuntimeWithLabelExposure tests exposure via label\n285: func TestAgentRuntimeWithLabelExposure(t *testing.T) {\n286:     client := setupE2EClient(t)\n287:     fixture := &AgentRuntimeFixtures{}\n288:     \n289:     labels := map[string]string{\n290:         \"agentcube/expose\": \"true\",\n291:     }\n292:     ar := fixture.NewAgentWithLabels(\"test-exposed-agent\", client.Namespace(), labels)\n293:     \n294:     // Create and wait\n295:     ctx := context.Background()\n296:     created, _ := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n297:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n298:     client.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, created.Name, 2*time.Minute)\n299:     \n300:     // Verify Router can route to this agent\n301:     resp, err := client.InvokeAgent(ctx, created.Name, map[string]interface{}{\"message\": \"hello\"})\n302:     require.NoError(t, err)\n303:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: #### 4.3.2 зҠ¶жҖҒеҗҢжӯҘжөӢиҜ• (`agents/agentruntime_status_test.go`)\n308: \n309: ```go\n310: // TestAgentRuntimeStatusSync tests status synchronization between pod and CRD\n311: func TestAgentRuntimeStatusSync(t *testing.T) {\n312:     client := setupE2EClient(t)\n313:     fixture := &AgentRuntimeFixtures{}\n314:     \n315:     ar := fixture.NewEchoAgent(\"test-status-sync\", client.Namespace())\n316:     ctx := context.Background()\n317:     \n318:     // Create\n319:     created, _ := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n320:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n321:     \n322:     // Watch status changes\n323:     watcher, err := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n324:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Watch(ctx, metav1.SingleObject(created.ObjectMeta))\n325:     require.NoError(t, err)\n326:     defer watcher.Stop()\n327:     \n328:     // Collect status updates\n329:     statusUpdates := []runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{}\n330:     timeout := time.After(3 * time.Minute)\n331:     \n332:     for {\n333:         select {\n334:         case event, ok := <-watcher.ResultChan():\n335:             if !ok {\n336:                 break\n337:             }\n338:             if ar, ok := event.Object.(*runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime); ok {\n339:                 statusUpdates = append(statusUpdates, ar.Status)\n340:                 if ar.Status.Ready {\n341:                     goto done\n342:                 }\n343:             }\n344:         case <-timeout:\n345:             t.Fatal(\"Timeout waiting for AgentRuntime to be ready\")\n346:         }\n347:     }\n348: done:\n349:     // Verify status progression\n350:     assert.GreaterOrEqual(t, len(statusUpdates), 1)\n351:     assert.True(t, statusUpdates[len(statusUpdates)-1].Ready)\n352: }\n353: ```\n354: \n355: #### 4.3.3 з”ҹе‘Ҫе‘ЁжңҹжөӢиҜ• (`agents/agentruntime_lifecycle_test.go`)\n356: \n357: ```go\n358: // TestAgentRuntimeUpdate tests updating an AgentRuntime\n359: func TestAgentRuntimeUpdate(t *testing.T) {\n360:     client := setupE2EClient(t)\n361:     fixture := &AgentRuntimeFixtures{}\n362:     \n363:     ar := fixture.NewEchoAgent(\"test-update\", client.Namespace())\n364:     ctx := context.Background()\n365:     \n366:     // Create\n367:     created, _ := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n368:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n369:     client.WaitForAgentRuntimeReady(ctx, created.Name, 2*time.Minute)\n370:     \n371:     // Update\n372:     created.Spec.SessionTimeout = \"10m\"\n373:     updated, err := client.RuntimeClient().RuntimeV1alpha1().\n374:         AgentRuntimes(client.Namespace()).Update(ctx, created, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n375:     require.NoError(t, err)\n376:     assert.Equal(t, \"10m\", updated.Spec.SessionTimeout)\n377: }\n378: \n379: // TestAgentRuntimeDelete tests deletion and cleanup\n380: func TestAgentRuntimeDelete(t *testing.T) {\n381:     client := setupE2EClient(t)\n382:     fixture := &AgentRuntimeFixtures{}\n383:     \n384:     ar := fixture.NewEchoAgent(